# =============================================================================
# Module 1 — Data Layer Environment Variables
# Neuro Honeypot Platform
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
#   1. Copy this file to .env in the same directory:
#        cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in all <generate-strong-password> placeholders with real values.
#      Use a password manager or: openssl rand -base64 32
#   3. NEVER commit .env to version control. The .gitignore in the repo root
#      must include '.env' (verify before pushing).
#   4. Store the generated values in your password manager before deploying.
#      If you lose POSTGRES_PASSWORD, you must rebuild the volume from scratch.
#
# PERMISSIONS:
#   chmod 600 .env
#   This file contains secrets — restrict read access to the operator only.
# =============================================================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PostgreSQL password for the 'honeypot' database user.
# Used by: PostgreSQL container (authentication), log-shipper (POSTGRES_DSN).
#
# Requirements:
#   - 32+ characters
#   - Mix of letters, numbers, and symbols (avoid @ and / which break DSN URLs)
#   - Example generator: openssl rand -base64 32 | tr -d '/+=@'
#
# This password appears in the log-shipper's POSTGRES_DSN environment variable:
#   POSTGRES_DSN=postgresql://honeypot:<this-value>@postgres:5432/honeypot
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=<generate-strong-password>
